il|website=G1}}</ref>\n| {{flagcountry|Brazil}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Supported devices ==\n<!-- Please only add devices that have Alexa built-in (allow interaction with Alexa), not devices that can be controlled using Alexa (devices that have Alexa skills) -->\n{{as of|2018|September}}, over 20,000 devices support interaction with Amazon Alexa.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/09/01/alexa-is-now-available-on-20000-devices/|title=Alexa is now available on 20,000 devices|last=Heater|first=Brian|date=1 September 2018|work=TechCrunch|access-date=1 September 2018|publisher=Oath Inc.}}</ref> Listed below are commercially available Alexa devices.\n\n=== Smart speakers ===\n* [[Amazon Echo]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Plus|Amazon Echo Plus]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Dot|Amazon Echo Dot]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Look|Amazon Echo Look]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Show|Amazon Echo Show]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Spot|Amazon Echo Spot]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Tap|Amazon Tap]]\n* [[Sonos One]] smart speaker<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/10/04/sonos-announces-alexa-controlled-wireless-speakers/|title=Sonos announces Alexa-controlled wireless speakers|last=Biggs|first=John|date=4 October 2017|work=TechCrunch|access-date=4 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sonos.com/en-gb/alexa-on-sonos|title=Alexa on Sonos {{!}} Sonos|website=Sonos|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-03-02}}</ref>\n* [[Lenovo Smart Assistant]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/2017/01/lenovos-smart-speaker-marries-alexa-smarts-hardon-karman-sounds/|title=Lenovo's Smart Speaker Marries Up Alexa Smarts and Harman Kardon Sounds|last=Barrett|first=Brian|date=3 January 2017|work=[[Wired (magazine)|Wired]]|access-date=3 October 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Harman Kardon]] Allure smart speaker<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/circuitbreaker/2017/8/31/16232912/harman-kardon-allure-alexa-speaker-cortana-speaker|title=Harman's Alexa speaker is 100x uglier than its Cortana speaker|last=Singleton|first=Micah|date=31 August 2017|work=The Verge|access-date=31 August 2017|publisher=Vox Media}}</ref>\n* [[Harman Kardon]] Astra smart speaker<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bizjournals.com/businesswire/press_releases/2018/02/27/20180227006499|title=HARMAN Adds Harman Kardon Astra with Amazon Alexa to Lineup of Voice Controlled Speakers|date=27 February 2018|work=[[American City Business Journals]]|access-date=2 March 2018}}</ref>\n* Kitsound Voice One smart speaker<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.pocket-lint.com/news/141800-kitsound-voice-one-gives-alexa-the-audio-oomph-she-needs|title=KitSound Voice One gives Alexa the audio oomph she needs|last=Langridge|first=Max|date=2 August 2017|work=Pocket-lint|access-date=}}</ref>\n* Eufy Genie (by [[Anker (electronics)|Anker]])<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://9to5toys.com/2017/08/09/anker-eufy-genie-alexa/|title=Anker's new Alexa-powered Eufy Genie undercuts Echo Dot on price|last=Daugherty|first=Trevor|date=9 August 2017|work=9to5Toys|access-date=9 August 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Invoxia Triby]]<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Bohn|first1=Dieter|title=This adorable Bluetooth speaker puts Alexa on your fridge|url=https://www.theverge.com/2016/4/28/11521976/triby-review-alexa-on-your-fridge|accessdate=8 September 2016|work=[[The Verge]]|publisher=[[Vox Media]]|date=28 April 2016}}</ref>\n* [[LG]] SmartThinQ Hub<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Torres|first1=Timothy|title=Eyes On: LG's SmartThinQ Hub With Alexa|url=https://www.pcmag.com/news/347593/eyes-on-lgs-smartthinq-hub-with-alexa|accessdate=9 September 2016|work=[[PC Magazine]]|date=3 September 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Onkyo]] VC-FLX1 smart speaker<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.techhive.com/article/3155092/consumer-electronics/onkyos-vc-flx1-smart-speaker-combines-alexa-sensors-and-a-webcam.html|title=Onkyo's VC-FLX1 smart speaker combines Alexa, sensors, and a webcam|date=6 January 2017|last=Nicolakis|first=Theo}}</ref>\n* Spark by Clazio touchscreen smart speaker{{ci