ld.com/article/20170516/entlife/305169931/|title=Element Integrates Amazon Fire TV Into New Sets|date=16 May 2017|work=[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]]|access-date=17 May 2017|language=en-US}}</ref>\n* [[Sony]] Smart TVs<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/alexa-is-coming-to-tvs-well-at-least-sony-smart-tvs/?ftag=CAD-04-10aai6f&bhid=25604195982914739067553674390171|title=Alexa is coming to Sony smart TVs|last=Kerr|first=Dara|date=20 September 2018|work=CNET|access-date=26 November 2018|publisher=CBS Interactive|last2=Fox Rubin|first2=Ben}}</ref>\n* [[Samsung]] Smart TVs (2019)\n\n=== Phones and tablets ===\n* [[Amazon Fire]] and [[Fire HD]] tablets - 4th, 5th, or 6th generation devices (limited features)<ref name=\"Amazon Help Supported Features\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=202013680 |title=Supported Alexa Features |website=Amazon |access-date=2017-04-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Amazon's new Fire HD 8 is its first tablet with Alexa|url=https://www.engadget.com/2016/09/08/amazon-fire-hd-8-tablet-with-alexa/|accessdate=8 September 2016|work=[[Engadget]]|date=8 September 2016}}</ref>\n* Fire 7, HD 8 & 10 - 7th generation<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.engadget.com/2017/09/19/amazon-unveils-fire-hd-10-tablet-with-hands-free-alexa/|title=Amazon's $150 Fire tablet summons Alexa hands-free|last=Fingas|first=Jon|date=19 September 2017|work=[[Engadget]]|access-date=21 September 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Huawei Mate 9]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pcmag.com/news/350816/huaweis-mate-9-becomes-the-first-alexa-phone|title=Huawei's Mate 9 Becomes the First Alexa Phone|last=|first=|date=|work=[[PC Magazine]]|newspaper=|access-date=9 January 2017|via=}}</ref>\n* [[HTC U11]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2017/05/htc-u11-hands-on-the-first-phone-with-both-google-and-alexa-voice-commands/|title=HTC U11 hands-on\u2014A squeezable, all-glass device with dual hotword support|work=[[Ars Tec