 above|last=Lavars|first=Nick|date=7 January 2018|work=New Atlas|access-date=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Kohler Co.]] Verdera Voice Lighted Mirror<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnkoetsier/2018/03/07/this-999-bathroom-mirror-is-alexa-powered-so-you-can-shop-while-you/|title=This $999 Bathroom Mirror Is Alexa-Powered So You Can Shop While You ...|last=Koetsier|first=John|date=7 March 2018|work=[[Forbes]]|access-date=11 March 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Netgear]] Orbi Voice Wi-Fi router<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gizmodo.com/netgear-stuffed-alexa-and-a-harman-kardon-speaker-into-1828693808|title=Netgear Stuffed Alexa and a Harman Kardon Speaker Into a Wifi Router For Some Reason|last=Clark Estes|first=Adam|date=30 August 2018|work=[[Gizmodo]]|access-date=30 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Wearables and earphones ===\n* OV by ONvocal headphones<ref name=\"14 December 2016\">{{Cite web|last1=Etherington|first1=Darrell|title=These new headphones let you talk to Amazon's Alexa anywhere you go|url=https://techcrunch.com/2016/12/14/these-new-headphones-let-you-talk-to-amazons-alexa-anywhere-you-go/|website=TechCrunch|accessdate=14 December 2016}}</ref>\n* Lynx robot<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://androidcentral.com/meet-lynx-walking-talking-robot-powered-amazon-alexa|title=Meet Lynx, the walking, talking home robot powered by Amazon Alexa|last=Lagace|first=Marc|date=6 January 2017|work=Android Central|access-date=9 January 2017|via=}}</ref>\n* [[Pebble (watch)#Pebble 2|Pebble Core]]<ref>{{Cite news|last1=Karcz|first1=Anthony|title=Pebble Core Becomes First 3G Ultraportable With Amazon Alexa|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/anthonykarcz/2016/06/03/pebble-core-amazon-alexa/|accessdate=8 September 2016|date=3 June 2016}}</ref> (cancelled due to [[Fitbit]] acquisition, product did not reach retail)\n* Orion Labs Onyx smart walkie-talkie<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Chokkattu|first1=Julian|title=Onyx communicator lets you talk to people around the globe with a push of a button|url=htt