, Echo devices, and Amazon Music in Mexico|last=Wiggers|first=Kyle|date=7 November 2018|work=[[VentureBeat]]|access-date=7 November 2018}}</ref>\n| {{flagcountry|Mexico}}\n|-\n|October 3, 2019<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{cite news |last1=Mari |first1=Angelica |title=Amazon kicks off Alexa trial in Brazil |url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/amazon-kicks-off-alexa-trial-in-brazil/ |accessdate=15 August 2019 |publisher=ZDNet |date=March 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://g1.globo.com/economia/tecnologia/noticia/2019/10/03/amazon-lanca-alexa-e-dispositivos-echo-no-brasil.ghtml|title=Amazon lan\u00e7a Alexa e dispositivos Echo no Brasil|website=G1}}</ref>\n| {{flagcountry|Brazil}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Supported devices ==\n<!-- Please only add devices that have Alexa built-in (allow interaction with Alexa), not devices that can be controlled using Alexa (devices that have Alexa skills) -->\n{{as of|2018|September}}, over 20,000 devices support interaction with Amazon Alexa.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/09/01/alexa-is-now-available-on-20000-devices/|title=Alexa is now available on 20,000 devices|last=Heater|first=Brian|date=1 September 2018|work=TechCrunch|access-date=1 September 2018|publisher=Oath Inc.}}</ref> Listed below are commercially available Alexa devices.\n\n=== Smart speakers ===\n* [[Amazon Echo]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Plus|Amazon Echo Plus]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Dot|Amazon Echo Dot]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Look|Amazon Echo Look]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Show|Amazon Echo Show]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Echo Spot|Amazon Echo Spot]]\n* [[Amazon Echo#Amazon Tap|Amazon Tap]]\n* [[Sonos One]] smart speaker<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2017/10/04/sonos-announces-alexa-controlled-wireless-speakers/|title=Sonos announces Alexa-controlled wireless speakers|last=Biggs|first=John|date=4 October 2017|work=TechCrunch|access-date=4 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sonos.com/en-gb/alexa-on-sonos|titl